data.content:
**Yes, C# fully supports `stackalloc`'d `Span<nint>` and `Span<nuint>`.** It works just like any other unmanaged type:

```csharp
Span<nint>  signed   = stackalloc nint[4];
Span<nuint> unsigned = stackalloc nuint[3];
```

The only hiccup was `sizeof(nint)` — since `nint`/`nuint` don't have a predefined size (they're pointer-width), `sizeof` requires an `unsafe` context. But `stackalloc` itself works fine in safe code. On this 64-bit machine, each element is 8 bytes.
